The paper discusses the performance analysis of biometric authentication systems based on secret key generation, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of stochastic decoders, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper deals with the storage and retrieval of biometric data, which can be considered as a topic related to cybersecurity (cs.CY). The use of biometric signals also suggests that the paper may be related to multimedia (cs.MM) and computer vision (cs.CV).
